01:51:02.520 --> 01:51:08.720
Because it's like, yeah, like DJ, we went to a theater.

01:51:08.720 --> 01:51:11.120
I mean, we went to a nightclub.

01:51:11.120 --> 01:51:14.280
And we talked to the owner.

01:51:14.280 --> 01:51:17.880
But they don't own it because it's owned by the state.

01:51:17.880 --> 01:51:21.440
But he said that we could put the DJ in at a certain time

01:51:21.440 --> 01:51:27.000
and not knowing that the DJ is part of the state, too.

01:51:27.000 --> 01:51:28.960
So we came in and we set up our stuff.

01:51:28.960 --> 01:51:30.640
And the owner said, we could do it.

01:51:30.640 --> 01:51:32.720
And the guy is like, he doesn't have no right to do this.

01:51:32.720 --> 01:51:35.120
And through our shit away and started,

01:51:35.120 --> 01:51:37.400
well, it's gotten to a fight with him because we thought,

01:51:37.400 --> 01:51:40.640
but it was just when you're in the US, you talk to the owner,

01:51:40.640 --> 01:51:43.560
the owner, who else do you talk to?

01:51:43.560 --> 01:51:46.480
But there you have to talk to the state.

01:51:46.480 --> 01:51:50.280
And so that was a little bit interesting, even for DJs.

01:51:50.280 --> 01:51:52.480
So they have everything really organized

01:51:52.480 --> 01:51:54.000
to umpteenth the green.

01:51:58.960 --> 01:51:59.960
Go ahead.

01:51:59.960 --> 01:52:00.960
Go ahead.

01:52:00.960 --> 01:52:04.960
When you were sending up, you were talking about the Rodney

01:52:04.960 --> 01:52:05.960
King decision.

01:52:05.960 --> 01:52:12.960
And you know, what it was like being here on the ground.

01:52:12.960 --> 01:52:14.960
What was your experience with that?

01:52:14.960 --> 01:52:15.960
With Rodney King?

01:52:15.960 --> 01:52:18.160
That moment, yeah.

01:52:18.160 --> 01:52:22.600
Well, the very first thing that happened was I was,

01:52:22.600 --> 01:52:25.960
we all couldn't, we thought that it was definitely

01:52:25.960 --> 01:52:28.640
going to be a guilty verdict.

01:52:28.640 --> 01:52:31.640
And so, I almost forgot about it.

01:52:31.640 --> 01:52:36.480
And so, I got off work and my wife came and got me.

01:52:36.480 --> 01:52:41.320
And she told me that Rodney King's guys who beating were

01:52:41.320 --> 01:52:43.640
released and were like, what?

01:52:43.640 --> 01:52:47.640
And I just rambled throughout the city.

01:52:47.640 --> 01:52:50.960
You know, I ran around and then we came here

01:52:50.960 --> 01:52:52.680
to our community.

01:52:52.680 --> 01:52:55.400
And people were really angry.

01:52:55.400 --> 01:52:57.400
This is really, really, really, really angry.

01:52:57.400 --> 01:53:02.800
They were befuddled, just running around, just like not

01:53:02.800 --> 01:53:06.120
knowing almost what to do, but angry, angry, angry.

01:53:06.120 --> 01:53:12.200
And I think the icon for me was to see a young white kid

01:53:12.200 --> 01:53:16.760
get off on the corner here and was apologizing to everybody.

01:53:16.760 --> 01:53:19.520
And then people were, didn't care.

01:53:19.520 --> 01:53:24.200
They were used to him as you know, he pushed out.

01:53:24.200 --> 01:53:27.800
And I told him, don't go further south.

01:53:27.800 --> 01:53:29.280
I said, don't go further south, man.

01:53:29.280 --> 01:53:30.720
He got in, went further south.

01:53:30.720 --> 01:53:32.080
So that was really deep.

01:53:32.080 --> 01:53:34.200
So I don't know what ever happened to him

01:53:34.200 --> 01:53:38.120
that he was candid up in the wrong kind of history

01:53:38.120 --> 01:53:40.880
to be in an all-black community.

01:53:40.880 --> 01:53:43.520
But I think he had the right attitude

01:53:43.520 --> 01:53:46.320
because he was like, I'm sorry, man, even though it isn't

01:53:46.320 --> 01:53:48.960
my fault, but I'm sorry, that's the dumbest thing

01:53:48.960 --> 01:53:51.200
that this country could ever have done.

01:53:51.200 --> 01:53:52.480
And so he dealt with it that way.

01:53:52.480 --> 01:53:54.520
So that was one of the icons for me.

01:53:54.520 --> 01:54:00.920
But then the next thing was the real paramilitary handling

01:54:00.920 --> 01:54:04.480
of it because I just wondered about all the burning.

01:54:04.480 --> 01:54:07.320
I am being a military before.

01:54:07.320 --> 01:54:10.240
I just know you can't.

01:54:10.240 --> 01:54:12.880
Building doesn't level in a couple hours.

01:54:12.880 --> 01:54:16.200
It doesn't burn down to a rubble in a few hours.

01:54:16.200 --> 01:54:22.320
So I think it would be like even myself,

01:54:22.320 --> 01:54:28.440
if I had to strike a fire inside a store and have it burn down,

01:54:28.440 --> 01:54:31.160
I wouldn't know how to really do it.

01:54:31.160 --> 01:54:38.680
It's a hard thing to burn, see it, and hard floors.

01:54:38.680 --> 01:54:42.040
And then to make it where it's so combustible that it burns it

01:54:42.040 --> 01:54:45.480
and burns it hard, all the infrastructure and stuff.

01:54:46.080 --> 01:54:48.760
Even if you threw gas around, it would just burn mostly

01:54:48.760 --> 01:54:51.200
the gas.

01:54:51.200 --> 01:54:54.920
It wouldn't burn the whole building that fast.

01:54:54.920 --> 01:54:56.400
I just can't see that.

01:54:56.400 --> 01:54:58.600
So I was noticing that as a real thing,

01:54:58.600 --> 01:55:01.480
it was really kind of strange.

01:55:01.480 --> 01:55:04.240
It was cathartic, a lot of people.

01:55:04.240 --> 01:55:06.680
And all the whole cultures, it wasn't just the black thing.

01:55:06.680 --> 01:55:09.240
It was a lot of people from Central America

01:55:09.240 --> 01:55:10.840
out here in the streets.

01:55:10.840 --> 01:55:13.320
And they were just this pissed off.

01:55:13.320 --> 01:55:14.960
And they were used to war zone.

01:55:14.960 --> 01:55:18.320
So they dealt with this pretty easily.

01:55:18.320 --> 01:55:21.560
Because I remember I was right here.

01:55:21.560 --> 01:55:24.520
And then I saw a couple of little ladies walking out

01:55:24.520 --> 01:55:25.480
and I missed all of this.

01:55:25.480 --> 01:55:29.320
And I was like, senior Rita, I'm not a very good night

01:55:29.320 --> 01:55:30.600
to be doing this.

01:55:30.600 --> 01:55:32.440
And she says, son, hello, right?

01:55:32.440 --> 01:55:33.440
It's all right.

01:55:33.440 --> 01:55:35.640
And then they went down there and I saw them next.

01:55:35.640 --> 01:55:40.840
And they had a couple of smirred off containers.

01:55:40.840 --> 01:55:43.920
You know, not just the bottles, but just the crates

01:55:43.920 --> 01:55:45.120
on top of their head.

01:55:45.120 --> 01:55:47.160
And they were taking this shit out.

01:55:47.160 --> 01:55:51.240
I was like, OK, go ahead on, y'all.

01:55:51.240 --> 01:55:55.240
I was like, so that was the kind of an indication of how

01:55:55.240 --> 01:55:56.560
it was just everybody.

01:55:56.560 --> 01:55:58.040
It was everybody was pretty pissed.

01:55:58.040 --> 01:56:02.480
And everybody took advantage of what was happening there.

01:56:02.480 --> 01:56:06.120
And then the following days were even worse.

01:56:06.120 --> 01:56:08.480
People just really, there was anarchy.

01:56:08.480 --> 01:56:11.560
I had never seen anarchy in full verge.

01:56:11.560 --> 01:56:15.400
But it was anarchy people were throwing things

01:56:15.400 --> 01:56:20.400
through picture windows and along the way, grabbing shit.

01:56:20.400 --> 01:56:25.000
In broad daylight, it was just kicking in things.

01:56:25.000 --> 01:56:28.560
And if someone grabbed them and stopped them,

01:56:28.560 --> 01:56:33.360
and we would stop them in places where we knew the people

01:56:33.360 --> 01:56:34.280
and stuff like that.

01:56:34.280 --> 01:56:35.520
But you couldn't do all of them.

01:56:35.520 --> 01:56:39.000
But so it was indiscriminate hitting sometimes, just

01:56:39.000 --> 01:56:41.520
like just boys being boys, you know, like with a bat

01:56:41.520 --> 01:56:44.880
just hitting shit and stuff like that.

01:56:44.880 --> 01:56:47.440
I was here guarding it.

01:56:47.440 --> 01:56:49.720
But people, for the most part, guarded it for me.

01:56:49.720 --> 01:56:53.440
And then we had another incident that was really interesting.

01:56:53.440 --> 01:56:55.840
We had a thing called a black gallery

01:56:55.840 --> 01:57:00.200
that had almost thousands and thousands of sculptures

01:57:00.200 --> 01:57:02.920
in it from Africa and all over the world.

01:57:02.920 --> 01:57:05.560
And the building next to it was in fire.

01:57:05.600 --> 01:57:10.720
And so everybody came from out of the residential neighborhoods

01:57:10.720 --> 01:57:16.360
and pulled them all out in the street and saved this place.

01:57:16.360 --> 01:57:17.280
It didn't burn.

01:57:17.280 --> 01:57:20.440
But then the following couple of days later,

01:57:20.440 --> 01:57:22.880
after they pulled everything, they helped them

01:57:22.880 --> 01:57:24.800
pull everything out and then put everything in.

01:57:24.800 --> 01:57:26.200
And not one thing was stolen.

01:57:26.200 --> 01:57:28.960
No way.

01:57:28.960 --> 01:57:32.240
So it was almost like people were almost like a tomatons

01:57:32.240 --> 01:57:34.120
drawn towards saving those things.

01:57:34.120 --> 01:57:37.280
They just came in and helped him pull out all those things

01:57:37.280 --> 01:57:40.720
because the fire looked like it was going to blow out

01:57:40.720 --> 01:57:41.840
that building.

01:57:41.840 --> 01:57:43.640
So things like that happen.

01:57:43.640 --> 01:57:47.000
The Korean family that was on the corner here, who still

01:57:47.000 --> 01:57:53.160
is here, they'll pull out a book.

01:57:53.160 --> 01:57:55.880
And they say, they have a whole place burning.

01:57:55.880 --> 01:57:59.240
This is the black families help me save my place.

01:57:59.240 --> 01:58:00.200
It was black people.

01:58:00.200 --> 01:58:04.080
So they were proud to let people know that all

01:58:04.080 --> 01:58:07.320
of us did because I went by there and they stay off this.

01:58:07.320 --> 01:58:08.280
These guys are cool.

01:58:08.280 --> 01:58:13.760
And they just leave them alone because the grocery store

01:58:13.760 --> 01:58:16.880
that went up the two days before that I saw him just

01:58:16.880 --> 01:58:19.240
knock somebody in the chest and say, get out of here.

01:58:19.240 --> 01:58:22.400
That kind of stuff just like really kind of evil stuff.

01:58:22.400 --> 01:58:26.120
Or you don't do that to a customer.

01:58:26.120 --> 01:58:29.360
No matter what kind of customer you grab them and hit them

01:58:29.360 --> 01:58:30.080
and stuff like that.

01:58:30.080 --> 01:58:34.400
So the Koreans have a short, just like black Americans.

01:58:34.400 --> 01:58:38.880
So it was pretty volatile with the two groups here.

01:58:38.880 --> 01:58:42.840
And I also had an insight with Koreans

01:58:42.840 --> 01:58:45.120
that's different than most people because they were my friends

01:58:45.120 --> 01:58:47.040
in Vietnam.

01:58:47.040 --> 01:58:50.160
And Koreans are considered the black people of Asia.

01:58:50.160 --> 01:58:53.000
And so there is a kind of a, they would say, me, you say, me,

01:58:53.000 --> 01:58:56.440
saying, GI, they would deal with us in the same kind

01:58:56.440 --> 01:58:59.760
of cultural way that was really respectful and felt

01:58:59.760 --> 01:59:01.360
similarity.

01:59:01.360 --> 01:59:03.760
So I was telling all the black people here

01:59:03.760 --> 01:59:05.720
that they really feel like they're us.

01:59:05.720 --> 01:59:08.680
So that's part of the reason they migrated to our neighborhoods

01:59:08.680 --> 01:59:11.840
because they also took care of us in Korea

01:59:11.840 --> 01:59:15.400
because all the army soldiers and those guys dated them.

01:59:15.400 --> 01:59:18.160
And so they knew us in that way.

01:59:18.160 --> 01:59:20.400
That's the reason that they're here.

01:59:20.400 --> 01:59:22.040
And they know how to braid your hair because they've

01:59:22.040 --> 01:59:25.920
created the hair in Korea.

01:59:25.920 --> 01:59:29.120
And they know how to take care of black hair and black bodies

01:59:29.120 --> 01:59:31.240
and the whole thing, which is kind of unusual.

01:59:31.240 --> 01:59:33.120
So they came here with a lot of skills

01:59:33.120 --> 01:59:35.480
and were able to undercut our market real well

01:59:35.480 --> 01:59:38.160
because it was outside money.

01:59:38.160 --> 01:59:40.120
And so that's what I'm learning.

01:59:40.120 --> 01:59:42.200
I don't blame things on folks.

01:59:42.200 --> 01:59:43.400
I'm more of just like learning.

01:59:43.400 --> 01:59:47.160
So that was what even that uprising was about for us

01:59:47.320 --> 01:59:51.320
to for me, the police thing that happened a year later

01:59:53.800 --> 01:59:55.680
with the police proving trying to prove

01:59:55.680 --> 01:59:57.720
that they are powerful like this.

01:59:57.720 --> 02:00:01.840
And you know, I must not 100% blame it on the police.

02:00:01.840 --> 02:00:04.520
And this is what we ended up studying with it

02:00:04.520 --> 02:00:06.880
because I have this friend Marcelina Morgan

02:00:06.880 --> 02:00:10.280
that ended up doing a study on that time period for me.

02:00:10.280 --> 02:00:14.600
And what she found was it was imitil again.

02:00:14.600 --> 02:00:16.680
It was the same thing that killed imitil.

02:00:16.760 --> 02:00:18.600
It was us that killed it.

02:00:18.600 --> 02:00:23.600
We whispered with this passive aggressive attitude

02:00:23.920 --> 02:00:28.920
about like did you see him hunting in around with that white girl

02:00:30.680 --> 02:00:34.000
and saying it loud enough so the master could hear it.

02:00:34.000 --> 02:00:36.480
And then like what like girl and find out

02:00:36.480 --> 02:00:38.720
that it was the grandfather that was hearing it

02:00:38.720 --> 02:00:41.800
and then he tells his son and he says,

02:00:41.800 --> 02:00:44.000
you know, he's been around all those news

02:00:44.000 --> 02:00:46.200
and he's up there doing this.

02:00:46.280 --> 02:00:48.520
And so that whisper came up to the point

02:00:48.520 --> 02:00:50.240
that it ended up killing a kid.

02:00:51.240 --> 02:00:52.600
It's the same thing that happened to us.

02:00:52.600 --> 02:00:56.920
They were they were they were cell phones were just coming in.

02:00:56.920 --> 02:01:01.120
So in gang banging with our kids and the all head hoods

02:01:01.120 --> 02:01:03.920
and they're all men standing on the corner

02:01:03.920 --> 02:01:05.400
and you saw how many of them were

02:01:05.400 --> 02:01:06.680
is just like a lot of kids.

02:01:06.680 --> 02:01:08.880
So we emancipated the street, you know,

02:01:08.880 --> 02:01:10.320
that was what we were trying to do

02:01:10.320 --> 02:01:13.320
because in the 80s they all got fearful of the street

02:01:13.320 --> 02:01:16.120
because there were people who were thinking drive-by's.

02:01:16.120 --> 02:01:18.840
But again, that was you know that that's what happened here

02:01:18.840 --> 02:01:23.040
was that it was the CIA agents came here to that theater

02:01:23.040 --> 02:01:25.760
and said that they caused all of that havoc in our neighborhood.

02:01:26.760 --> 02:01:28.840
They announced it saying that it was

02:01:28.840 --> 02:01:30.640
because it was a part of the problem.

02:01:30.640 --> 02:01:32.680
Imagine kids who don't have sense

02:01:32.680 --> 02:01:35.640
like these cars, I mean like the burning down

02:01:35.640 --> 02:01:37.800
of these buildings when they don't have that skill.

02:01:37.800 --> 02:01:40.160
You know, then the second thing

02:01:40.160 --> 02:01:45.160
who has exporting and importing capabilities

02:01:45.880 --> 02:01:48.120
from Central America and bringing in crack here.

02:01:50.120 --> 02:01:52.000
And they don't have no airplanes,

02:01:52.000 --> 02:01:53.920
they don't have any airplane skills, you know,

02:01:53.920 --> 02:01:56.640
nobody's bringing it in on the ground.

02:01:56.640 --> 02:02:00.200
They're not bringing boats through how does it get here?

02:02:00.200 --> 02:02:02.400
Got here through the agents, you know.

02:02:02.400 --> 02:02:03.760
And they admitted it.

02:02:03.760 --> 02:02:06.560
And so this whole neighborhood when we call

02:02:06.560 --> 02:02:09.800
and some of the early studies by the guys

02:02:09.800 --> 02:02:11.960
from Martin Luther King, all the doctors,

02:02:11.960 --> 02:02:15.920
they were all saying that this whole gang thing was made up.

02:02:17.480 --> 02:02:19.160
And I know it's hard to believe,

02:02:19.160 --> 02:02:22.560
but the thing that they would say is just this is like,

02:02:23.520 --> 02:02:25.040
you look at a gang and you look

02:02:25.040 --> 02:02:28.000
all internationally organized they are,

02:02:28.000 --> 02:02:31.120
their black churches aren't that well organized.

02:02:31.120 --> 02:02:33.280
And it's the most organized thing we have.

02:02:33.280 --> 02:02:36.360
And then so how did these kids get all of this organizing

02:02:36.360 --> 02:02:37.760
skills all of a sudden?

02:02:37.760 --> 02:02:39.240
Out of prison, come on.

02:02:40.360 --> 02:02:41.280
You know?

02:02:41.280 --> 02:02:45.920
And then the other thing is a military man is shooting, you know?

02:02:45.920 --> 02:02:48.440
When they were first killing who they shot at

02:02:48.440 --> 02:02:50.160
and both of the people are moving,

02:02:51.480 --> 02:02:53.680
you can't transact, you know,

02:02:53.680 --> 02:02:57.360
you have to be a super sniper to be moving

02:02:57.360 --> 02:03:00.040
and hit a moving object, you know?

02:03:00.040 --> 02:03:02.640
And you almost can't even do it with a machine gun.

02:03:04.400 --> 02:03:06.480
So those are little things that came out in my brain

02:03:06.480 --> 02:03:08.480
and they made me go, oh, that's a little bit different.

02:03:08.480 --> 02:03:09.600
So I asked the kids, you know,

02:03:09.600 --> 02:03:10.960
and they were shooting, did,

02:03:10.960 --> 02:03:12.560
were they trying to hit him?

02:03:12.560 --> 02:03:14.080
And they were like, yeah, oh, like,

02:03:14.080 --> 02:03:15.440
and they were moving to it?

02:03:15.440 --> 02:03:17.920
Oh, wow, that's a little bit deep.

02:03:17.920 --> 02:03:19.440
Cause in order to really do that,

02:03:19.440 --> 02:03:21.960
you have to shoot thousands and thousands and thousands

02:03:21.960 --> 02:03:24.880
of bullets to be able to be that much of a marksman,

02:03:24.880 --> 02:03:26.120
marksman, you know?

02:03:26.120 --> 02:03:27.720
And they don't have that much money.

02:03:28.760 --> 02:03:31.720
So all those things are the things that made me go home.

02:03:31.720 --> 02:03:34.560
I don't have an answer for it, but it did make me go home.

02:03:34.560 --> 02:03:36.440
I don't know, I don't know what the answer is,

02:03:36.440 --> 02:03:40.320
but I know that it's more than just these guys here

02:03:40.320 --> 02:03:41.440
in this neighborhood.

02:03:41.440 --> 02:03:42.440
Yeah.

02:03:42.440 --> 02:03:44.440
Did you feel any of this?

02:03:44.440 --> 02:03:46.440
Because it's all my friends?

02:03:46.440 --> 02:03:48.040
Did you ever ask?

02:03:48.040 --> 02:03:50.600
Of the uprising, no, I didn't.

02:03:50.600 --> 02:03:55.600
I was, I, I, at that time viewed it almost like a birth,

02:03:56.640 --> 02:04:00.200
you know, I really thought it was like intrusing on people

02:04:00.200 --> 02:04:05.200
while they were just getting authority of the energy out.

02:04:05.600 --> 02:04:09.160
And it was, it was a time that to me, my,

02:04:09.160 --> 02:04:12.720
I know most of my political friends couldn't understand it,

02:04:12.720 --> 02:04:14.920
but I'm just not that kind of person.

02:04:14.920 --> 02:04:16.120
I don't like shooting.

02:04:16.120 --> 02:04:19.800
Cause even homelessness, I, I was asked to do projects on that.

02:04:19.800 --> 02:04:23.480
I can't shoot a mother scrambling little ass five hour,

02:04:23.480 --> 02:04:27.120
you know, to get her kids fed and find a place to sleep

02:04:27.120 --> 02:04:30.880
and in a danky ass downtown in the first place.

02:04:30.880 --> 02:04:34.160
And so it just, it doesn't push good buttons in me.

02:04:34.200 --> 02:04:35.520
And I don't even work in prisons.

02:04:35.520 --> 02:04:39.320
I hate working in prisons because I had a job on doing that

02:04:39.320 --> 02:04:42.640
and I just can't last too long when people are in prison.

02:04:42.640 --> 02:04:46.160
I can't shoot people like in an animal state of being.

02:04:46.160 --> 02:04:48.920
And even if it helps them out of it,

02:04:48.920 --> 02:04:52.240
I, I can't put myself in that animal state of being

02:04:52.240 --> 02:04:54.440
to, to shoot them in that way.

02:04:54.440 --> 02:04:58.960
It's just, and so I, I rather just tell stories about it

02:04:58.960 --> 02:05:01.520
cause we will use a prison and tell a story

02:05:01.520 --> 02:05:02.920
about a person in prison.

02:05:02.920 --> 02:05:05.360
But I, but to shoot a real live person

02:05:05.360 --> 02:05:10.240
that has to live through that whole, whole degrading experience

02:05:10.240 --> 02:05:12.800
and the document and by high behind bars and stuff.

02:05:12.800 --> 02:05:14.440
I've never been able to really do that.

02:05:14.440 --> 02:05:15.640
You know what?

02:05:15.640 --> 02:05:17.920
So that, that's my kind of foil,

02:05:17.920 --> 02:05:21.320
but I am not into doing that.

02:05:21.320 --> 02:05:23.680
So that was what, that's what happened with that.

02:05:23.680 --> 02:05:27.480
So, but what I ended up doing about it is I did it,

02:05:27.480 --> 02:05:29.320
I did do a piece now that I think about it.

02:05:29.320 --> 02:05:32.040
I did a piece called Word Sound and Power

02:05:32.040 --> 02:05:34.960
and I did it for Channel 28.

02:05:34.960 --> 02:05:39.960
And, and so my focus was then to show how powerful art was,

02:05:39.960 --> 02:05:44.000
you know, so that art, art places where they only place

02:05:44.000 --> 02:05:46.560
not attack, you know, because we have a sense

02:05:46.560 --> 02:05:47.920
of working with the community.

02:05:47.920 --> 02:05:52.320
And then we made poems out of the stories,

02:05:52.320 --> 02:05:54.600
you know, made music out of it.

02:05:54.600 --> 02:05:58.280
And so that was how I dealt with it is the whole idea

02:05:58.280 --> 02:06:02.000
of how we deal with compost and put flowers in it, you know.

02:06:02.160 --> 02:06:04.720
So that was more, again, how I dealt with it.

02:06:04.720 --> 02:06:06.720
And it is too nice of a way for some people

02:06:06.720 --> 02:06:09.640
because they wanted to see the dirt and grime of it all.

02:06:09.640 --> 02:06:13.640
But I tended, I tend not to tackle things that way.

02:06:13.640 --> 02:06:18.040
Because even with my story on I and I, that, that piece,

02:06:18.040 --> 02:06:21.440
it was about an African-Wing goddess coming to see her people.

02:06:21.440 --> 02:06:23.560
So that was what some of my friends would say,

02:06:23.560 --> 02:06:24.800
how come she's not dirty?

02:06:24.800 --> 02:06:27.960
She's not, what a kind of revolutionary dirty.

02:06:27.960 --> 02:06:31.520
I was like, that's not how I, here she's a goddess, you know.

02:06:31.520 --> 02:06:34.320
So, but, so that's my differentness.

02:06:34.320 --> 02:06:36.680
And I used to always have a fight with a lot of the guys

02:06:36.680 --> 02:06:39.800
because even if some of the guys who were

02:06:41.000 --> 02:06:43.640
called themselves revolutionaries and they were the lie

02:06:43.640 --> 02:06:46.480
on dude like communism, and I would say, I don't like communism.

02:06:46.480 --> 02:06:47.640
And they were like, why?

02:06:47.640 --> 02:06:51.640
Like, I read the Communist manifesto and it said,

02:06:51.640 --> 02:06:53.920
the lumpkin proletariat lives off the state

02:06:53.920 --> 02:06:55.880
and that's my mama, you know.

02:06:55.880 --> 02:06:59.280
So how am I, you know, they're saying that we're,

02:06:59.400 --> 02:07:02.040
that's the nastiness of the earth.

02:07:02.040 --> 02:07:03.640
You know, like, well, that's not really,

02:07:03.640 --> 02:07:06.080
but I'm like, that's what I read, you know, I don't know,

02:07:06.080 --> 02:07:09.240
you know, that you can say that he really didn't mean

02:07:09.240 --> 02:07:11.440
your mama, but that's what I read.

02:07:11.440 --> 02:07:15.840
You know, and so I don't see what's so good about that system.

02:07:15.840 --> 02:07:18.800
And then when I met communist, they were more bureaucratic

02:07:18.800 --> 02:07:23.080
and harder and not nice people and they were,

02:07:23.080 --> 02:07:24.680
they were very racist themselves.

02:07:24.680 --> 02:07:28.200
So I mean, I didn't see what was so good about that whole movement.

02:07:28.200 --> 02:07:30.520
So I never aligned with it.

02:07:30.520 --> 02:07:34.440
And I have always, like, like I said, I've always,

02:07:34.440 --> 02:07:37.600
this has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

02:07:37.600 --> 02:07:39.720
and the Smithsonian National Museum

02:07:39.720 --> 02:07:42.360
of African American History and Culture.

